'''St. Louis Blues vs. Calgary Flames'''

In Game 6, the Flames led 4–1 after two periods and 5–2 early in the third, but the Blues came back to tie it and then won on an overtime goal by [[Doug Wickenheiser]].  In Game 7, the Flames were up 2–0 before the Blues scored in the third to cut the lead in half.  There wouldn't be another comeback, though, as [[Mike Vernon (ice hockey)|Mike Vernon]] and the Flames withstood a late assault to advance to their first Stanley Cup Final.
